{"lemma":"تَعْسُ","slug":"تَعْسُ","root":"ت.ع.س","root_slug":"ت-ع-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ع-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تَعْس","root":"تعس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3956","n3957","n3958"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to perish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become miserable, to become wretched"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to stumble and fall on one's face"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to destroy, to ruin, to kill","examples":[{"text":"تَعَسَهَا ٱلْمَرَضُ","english":"The decease killed her."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَعَسَ (taʕasa) and تَعِسَ (taʕisa, “to perish; to become miserable; to stumble”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَعَسَ (taʕasa, “to destroy; to ruin”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَعَسَ (taʕasa) and تَعِسَ (taʕisa, “to perish; to become miserable; to stumble”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ta.ʕa.sa/","/ta.ʕi.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3956","headword_ar":"تَعَسَ","root":"tEs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEosN","text_ar":"تَعْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, Msb, K, &c.;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEsa","text_ar":"تَعسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sh, AHeyth, A, IAth, K;) but the latter is not chaste; (A, TA;) or the former is used in addressing a person, saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEasota","text_ar":"تَعَسْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the latter, in narration; (K;) accord. to Sh; but ISd says that this is strange; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fell, having stumbled; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AinotaEa$a","text_ar":"اِنْتَعَشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": this is the primary signification: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he stumbled and fell"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, A, IAth, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his hands and mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he fell upon his face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rustamee, Msb, TA:) [and this may also be meant by one of the explanations of the inf. n. in the TA, which is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nukosN fiY safaAlK","text_ar":"نُكْسٌ فِى سَفَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he fell in any manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) You say, by way of imprecation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEasa waA@notakasa","text_ar":"تَعَسَ وَا@نْتَكَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May he fall upon his face, and not rise after his fall until he fall a second time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEasa","text_ar":"تَعَسَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"famaA A@notaEa$a wa$iyka falaA A@notaqa$a","text_ar":"فَمَا ا@نْتَعَشَ وَشِيكَ فَلَا ا@نْتَقَشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May he fall, having stumbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stumble and fall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and not rise again; and may he be pricked with a thorn, and not extract the thorn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And accord. to certain of the Kilábees,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEasa","text_ar":"تَعَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He missed his proof in litigation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the object of his search in seeking."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He perished."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-'Amr Ibn-El-'Alà, S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEasota","text_ar":"تَعَسْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as though meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mayest thou perish."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became far removed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became lowered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"degraded."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEasa jad~uhu","text_ar":"تَعَسَ جَدُّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune, fell:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may his fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune, fall"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Evr","text_ar":"عثر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEasahu A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"تَعَسَهُ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEosN","text_ar":"تَعْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] (A'Obeyd, A, Msb, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AtEshu","text_ar":"اتعسهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AHeyth, S, A, Msb, K;) the former unknown to Sb; (Az, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made him to fall, having stumbled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to stumble and fall"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his hands and mouth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHeyth, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his"},{"kind":"page_break","n":308},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to fall upon his face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to fall in any manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God destroyed him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made him to perish."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, S, K.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made him to become far removed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God lowered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"degraded, him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b5-  You say, by way of imprecation,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEosFA lahu","text_ar":"تَعْسًا لَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May he"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fall, having stumbled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stumble and fall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stumble and fall upon his hands and mouth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon his face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fall upon his face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God make destruction to cleave to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may God destroy him."},{"kind":"text","text":"] Aboo-Is-hák says, in explanation of the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fataEosFA lahumo","text_ar":"فَتَعْسًا لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xlvii. 9, that it may be in the accus. case as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atoEasahumu","text_ar":"اَتْعَسَهُمُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) A man also says, by way of imprecation, to his swift and excellent camel, when it stumbles,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEosFA","text_ar":"تَعْسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God throw thee down upon thy nostrils:"},{"kind":"text","text":"expressing his disapproval of the stumbling of a beast of such age and strength: but if it be not a swift and excellent beast, and stumble, he says to it"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEFA","text_ar":"لَعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atoEasa","text_ar":"اَتْعَسَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~ahu","text_ar":"جَدَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God make his fortune,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune, to sink!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A.)"}],"source_refs":["S","AHeyth","A","IAth","K","TA","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n3957","headword_ar":"تَعْسٌ","root":"tEs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1 [which see, throughout]. ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil; mischief."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3958","headword_ar":"تَعِسٌ","root":"tEs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}